Adversary Emulation with Atomic Red Team
Objectives
By the end of this lab, students will be able to:

Install and configure Atomic Red Team framework for adversary emulation
Execute MITRE ATT&CK technique simulations
Implement detection rules for emulated attacks
Create Python automation scripts for testing and detection
Analyze attack artifacts and detection results
Prerequisites
Basic Linux command line proficiency
Understanding of MITRE ATT&CK framework
Python programming fundamentals
Familiarity with YAML file format
Basic cybersecurity concepts
Lab Environment
This lab uses Al Nafi's pre-configured Linux cloud machines. Click Start Lab to access your environment with all necessary tools pre-installed.

Task 1: Install and Configure Atomic Red Team
Step 1: Install Dependencies
Update system and install required packages:

sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade -y
sudo apt install -y git curl wget python3 python3-pip powershell unzip jq
pip3 install pyyaml requests pandas
Step 2: Clone Atomic Red Team Repository
cd /opt
sudo git clone https://github.com/redcanaryco/atomic-red-team.git
sudo chown -R $USER:$USER /opt/atomic-red-team
Step 3: Install PowerShell Module
Launch PowerShell and install the Invoke-AtomicRedTeam module:

pwsh
Inside PowerShell:

Install-Module -Name invoke-atomicredteam,powershell-yaml -Force
Import-Module invoke-atomicredteam
exit
Step 4: Create Lab Directory Structure
mkdir -p ~/art-lab/{logs,scripts,detection-rules,results}
cd ~/art-lab
Step 5: Verify Installation
Test the installation:

pwsh -Command "Import-Module invoke-atomicredteam; Get-Command Invoke-AtomicTest"
