Troubleshooting Tips
PowerShell Module Issues:

Verify PowerShell version: pwsh --version
Reinstall module: Install-Module -Name invoke-atomicredteam -Force
Check module path: $env:PSModulePath
Permission Errors:

Ensure proper ownership: sudo chown -R $USER:$USER /opt/atomic-red-team
Check script permissions: chmod +x ~/art-lab/scripts/*.py
Detection Not Working:

Verify log files exist: ls -lh ~/art-lab/logs/
Check YAML syntax: python3 -c "import yaml; yaml.safe_load(open('detection-rules/suspicious_process.yml'))"
Ensure log collector is running: ps aux | grep log_collector
Conclusion
This lab demonstrated adversary emulation using Atomic Red Team and custom detection mechanisms. You learned to simulate MITRE ATT&CK techniques, collect relevant logs, and implement detection rules. This purple team approach helps validate security controls and improve detection capabilities. Continue practicing with additional techniques and refining detection rules to enhance your defensive security skills.
